Marketplace._purchase via buyItem
├── when the item does not exist
│   └── it should revert with ItemDoesNotExist
└── when the item exists
    ├── given the buyer is the seller
    │   └── it should revert with SellerCannotBuyOwnItem
    ├── given the item's payment token is disabled
    │   └── it should revert with TokenNotAccepted
    └── given the buyer is not the seller and the payment token is enabled
        ├── given the buyer allowance is less than price plus fee
        │   └── it should revert with InsufficientAllowance
        ├── given the buyer balance is less than price plus fee
        │   └── it should revert with InsufficientBalance
        ├── given the buyer already has access
        │   └── it should revert with AlreadyHasAccess
        └── given the buyer does not have access
            ├── given feeBps is greater than zero
            │   ├── when this is the first purchase
            │   │   └── it should grant access, increment purchaseCount, emit ItemFrozenAfterSale and ItemPurchased, and transfer fee plus seller proceeds
            │   └── when this is a later purchase by a distinct buyer
            │       └── it should grant access, increment purchaseCount, and keep the item frozen without another state transition
            └── given feeBps is zero
                └── it should grant access, emit ItemPurchased with zero fee, pay only the seller, and leave the fee recipient balance unchanged
